librjss(1)                  General Commands Manual                 librjss(1)

NAME
     librjss – Robust async Rust client for Juragan Subsystem (JSS) /
               Frappe / ERPNext APIs.

SYNOPSIS
     [dependencies]
     librjss = { git = "https://github.com/mroczect/librjss.git" }

     use librjss::{
         RjssClient, ClientConfig, AuthMode, JssError,
         SessionInfo, FrappeBoot, BootUser, BootUserInfo,
         SidebarPages, NavbarSettings, FrequentLink,
         UserInfo, ReportMeta, AppData,
     };

DESCRIPTION
     librjss provides full access to a JSS (Frappe) server, featuring:

        • Cookie-based session authentication and token-based API key/secret
          authentication.
        • Automatic CSRF token extraction from the /app dashboard.
        • Configurable retry with exponential backoff.
        • Typed builders for report execution, doctype CRUD, and file
          upload/download.
        • A rich error model that mirrors Frappe JSON error responses.
        • Zero-framework – lightweight dependencies on reqwest, serde,
          secrecy, and a few other small crates.
        • Unique trace ID per client for distributed tracing.

     This manual documents every public module, struct, enum, trait, and
     method.

INSTALLATION
     Add the dependency to your Cargo.toml:

         [dependencies]
         librjss = { git = "https://github.com/mroczect/librjss.git" }

     No feature flags are required for basic usage.

QUICK START – CLI BINARY
     A minimal CLI binary is included at src/bin/cli_auth.rs.

     Build and run with environment variables:

         export JSS_BASE_URL=https://app.juragansejati.biz.id
         export JSS_EMAIL=user@example.com
         export JSS_PASSWORD=password

         cargo run --bin cli_auth

     For token authentication, set JSS_TOKEN_API_KEY and
     JSS_TOKEN_API_SECRET instead of email/password.

