CORE CONCEPTS

   RjssClient
       Central struct holding configuration, HTTP client, session,
       credentials, and boot data.

       Constructor:
           RjssClient::new(config: ClientConfig) -> Result<Self, JssError>
           Validates configuration, builds a reqwest client with a cookie
           jar, timeout, and user-agent.

       Public methods:

       Authentication & session
           authenticate(&mut self) -> Result<(), JssError>
               Logs in using session or token (depending on AuthMode). In
               session mode it stores credentials and calls login. Token
               mode directly constructs a synthetic SessionInfo.

           logout(&mut self) -> Result<(), JssError>
               Only meaningful for AuthMode::Session. Sends a logout
               request with the CSRF token, then clears session and
               credentials.

           ensure_session(&mut self) -> Result<(), JssError>
               Checks whether the current session is still valid by
               calling get_logged_user. If a 401 is returned the session
               is discarded and, if credentials are available, a fresh
               login is performed automatically.

       Accessors
           session_info(&self) -> Option<&SessionInfo>
               Returns a reference to the current session data.

           boot(&self) -> Option<&FrappeBoot>
               Returns the boot data extracted from the /app page after
               login. Contains user info, permissions, sidebar, etc.

           base_url(&self) -> &Url
               The base server URL in use.

           trace_id(&self) -> &str
               Unique UUID v4 identifier for tracing/logging.

       Authenticated HTTP requests
           authenticated_get(&self, path: &str) -> Result<String, JssError>
           authenticated_post(&self, path: &str, body_json: &str) -> Result<String, JssError>
           authenticated_put(&self, path: &str, body_json: &str) -> Result<String, JssError>
           authenticated_delete(&self, path: &str) -> Result<String, JssError>
               Each sends a GET/POST/PUT/DELETE request to the path joined
               with base_url. They attach the appropriate authorization
               header (token or CSRF) and handle retry with exponential
               backoff.

       File operations
           upload_file(&self, file_name: &str, file_content: Vec<u8>,
                        doctype: &str, docname: &str, fieldname: &str)
               -> Result<String, JssError>
               Uploads a file to /api/method/upload_file using
               multipart/form-data. Returns the raw JSON response.

           download_file(&self, file_url: &str) -> Result<Vec<u8>, JssError>
               Downloads a file from a relative URL (e.g., "/files/photo.png").
               Returns raw bytes.

           download_file_to_path(&self, file_url: &str, save_path: &Path)
               -> Result<(), JssError>
               Same as above, but writes directly to disk.

       Report builder
           report(&self, name: &str) -> ReportBuilder<'_>
               Returns a builder for running a named Frappe report.

       Doctype / resource builder
           doctype(&self, name: &str) -> ResourceBuilder<'_>
               Builder for fetching document lists.

           get_doc(&self, doctype: &str, name: &str) -> Result<String, JssError>
               Fetches a single document by name.

           create_doc(&self, doctype: &str, data: &impl Serialize) -> Result<String, JssError>
               Creates a new document. `data` must be serializable to JSON.

           update_doc(&self, doctype: &str, name: &str, data: &impl Serialize) -> Result<String, JssError>
               Updates an existing document.

           delete_doc(&self, doctype: &str, name: &str) -> Result<String, JssError>
               Deletes a document.

           call_method(&self, method: &str, args: Option<HashMap<String, String>>) -> Result<String, JssError>
               Calls a whitelisted server method (e.g., frappe.email.send)
               with optional arguments. The body is sent as a JSON POST.

       Boot data accessors (convenience)
           user_info_map(&self) -> Option<&HashMap<String, BootUserInfo>>
           sidebar_pages(&self) -> Option<&SidebarPages>
           navbar_settings(&self) -> Option<&NavbarSettings>
           versions(&self) -> Option<&HashMap<String, String>>
           lang_dict(&self) -> Option<&HashMap<String, String>>
           frequent_links(&self) -> Option<&[FrequentLink]>
           is_developer_mode(&self) -> bool
           is_read_only(&self) -> bool

           All return data taken from frappe.boot after login.
           `is_developer_mode` returns true when `developer_mode != 0`.
           `is_read_only` is taken directly from the `read_only` field.

       Trait implementation
           AuthEndpoints is implemented for RjssClient, allowing static URL
           builders to be called through the type.

   AuthMode (enum)
       Authentication strategy selection.

           pub enum AuthMode {
               Session {
                   email: secrecy::SecretString,
                   password: secrecy::SecretString,
               },
               Token {
                   api_key: String,
                   api_secret: secrecy::SecretString,
               },
           }

       • Session – logs in with email/password, manages session cookies,
         and automatically extracts the CSRF token from /app.
       • Token – sends an Authorization: token api_key:api_secret header
         on every request. No explicit login or logout is required.

   ClientConfig
       Configuration container validated at client creation.

           pub struct ClientConfig {
               pub base_url: reqwest::Url,
               pub auth_mode: AuthMode,
               pub expected_sitename: Option<String>,
               pub required_roles: Vec<String>,
               pub timeout_secs: u64,          // default 30
               pub max_retries: u32,           // default 3
               pub user_agent: String,
               pub insecure_ssl: bool,         // default false
           }

       Method:
           validate(&self) -> Result<(), JssError>
               Ensures:
                 • HTTPS is used unless insecure_ssl = true.
                 • In AuthMode::Session, email and password are not empty.

   JssError
       Comprehensive error type covering all failure modes.

           pub enum JssError {
               Config(String),
               Validation(String),
               Network(reqwest::Error),
               Http { status: StatusCode, body: String },
               ApiError {
                   exc_type: String,
                   message: String,
                   status: StatusCode,
               },
               Auth(String),
               Csrf(String),
               Permission(String),
               SitenameMismatch { expected: String, actual: String },
               NotAuthenticated,
               RateLimited { retry_after: Option<u64> },
               Parse(String),
               Expired,
               Cancelled,
               FileOperation(String),
               Internal(String),
           }

       Helper methods:
           from_api_response(status: StatusCode, body: &str) -> JssError
               Parses a Frappe JSON error body. If exc_type is present,
               returns ApiError; otherwise returns Http.

           status_code(&self) -> StatusCode
               Maps each variant to an appropriate HTTP status code, e.g.:
                 Config/Validation/Internal → 500
                 Network → 502
                 Auth/NotAuthenticated/Expired → 401
                 Csrf/Permission/SitenameMismatch → 403
                 RateLimited → 429
                 Parse/FileOperation → 500

   SessionInfo
       Session data stored after a successful login.

           pub struct SessionInfo {
               pub sid: secrecy::SecretString,
               pub csrf_token: secrecy::SecretString,
               pub full_name: Option<String>,
               pub sitename: String,
               pub roles: Vec<String>,
           }

       • sid – session ID from the login response.
       • csrf_token – token extracted from the /app page.
       • full_name – user’s full name (from boot or login response).
       • sitename – site name from frappe.boot.
       • roles – user role list.

   FrappeBoot and related types
       Data structure deserialized from the JavaScript `frappe.boot`
       object on the /app page. All fields have defaults (mostly Option
       or empty collections).

       FrappeBoot (handler::types::boot)
           pub struct FrappeBoot {
               pub user: BootUser,
               pub sitename: String,
               pub csrf_token: String,
               pub sysdefaults: SysDefaults,
               pub app_logo_url: Option<String>,
               pub home_page: Option<String>,
               pub allow_modules: Vec<String>,
               pub can_select: Vec<String>,
               pub can_create: Vec<String>,
               pub can_write: Vec<String>,
               pub can_read: Vec<String>,
               pub can_submit: Vec<String>,
               pub can_cancel: Vec<String>,
               pub can_delete: Vec<String>,
               pub can_get_report: Vec<String>,
               pub all_reports: HashMap<String, ReportMeta>,
               pub module_wise_workspaces: HashMap<String, Vec<String>>,
               pub dashboards: Vec<DashboardMeta>,
               pub single_types: Vec<String>,
               pub calendars: Vec<String>,
               pub treeviews: Vec<String>,
               pub module_app: HashMap<String, String>,
               pub app_data: Vec<AppData>,
               pub user_info: HashMap<String, BootUserInfo>,
               pub sidebar_pages: SidebarPages,
               pub navbar_settings: Option<NavbarSettings>,
               pub versions: HashMap<String, String>,
               pub lang_dict: HashMap<String, String>,
               pub lang: Option<String>,
               pub timezone_info: Option<serde_json::Value>,
               pub page_info: HashMap<String, PageInfo>,
               pub frequently_visited_links: Vec<FrequentLink>,
               pub developer_mode: i32,
               pub read_only: bool,
               pub socketio_port: Option<u16>,
               pub desk_settings: HashMap<String, serde_json::Value>,
               pub desk_theme: Option<String>,
           }

       BootUser
           pub struct BootUser {
               pub name: String,
               pub email: String,
               pub full_name: String,
               pub roles: Vec<String>,
               pub allow_modules: Vec<String>,
               pub user_type: String,
               pub permissions: HashMap<String, Vec<String>>,
               pub can_select: Vec<String>,
               pub can_create: Vec<String>,
               pub can_write: Vec<String>,
               pub can_read: Vec<String>,
               pub can_submit: Vec<String>,
               pub can_cancel: Vec<String>,
               pub can_delete: Vec<String>,
               pub can_get_report: Vec<String>,
               pub all_reports: HashMap<String, ReportMeta>,
           }

       SysDefaults
           pub struct SysDefaults {
               pub default_app: Option<String>,
               pub time_zone: Option<String>,
           }

       ReportMeta
           pub struct ReportMeta {
               pub modified: String,
               pub title: String,
               pub ref_doctype: String,
               pub report_type: String,
           }

       DashboardMeta { pub name: String }
       AppData { pub app_name, app_title, app_route, app_logo_url: Value,
                 modules, workspaces }

       BootUserInfo
           pub struct BootUserInfo {
               pub fullname: String,
               pub image: Option<String>,
               pub name: String,
               pub email: String,
               pub time_zone: Option<String>,
           }

       SidebarPages
           pub struct SidebarPages {
               pub workspace_setup_completed: Option<i32>,
               pub pages: Vec<SidebarPage>,
               pub has_access: bool,
               pub has_create_access: bool,
           }

       SidebarPage (numerous fields, see source)

       NavbarSettings { pub settings_dropdown, help_dropdown: Vec<NavbarItem> }
       NavbarItem { pub item_label, item_type, action, route, hidden,
                    is_standard }
       PageInfo { pub title: Option<String>, modified: Option<String> }
       FrequentLink { pub route: String, count: i32 }

   AuthEndpoints (trait)
       Implemented by RjssClient. Provides static URL builders that can
       be used without a client instance.

           pub trait AuthEndpoints {
               fn login_url(base: &Url) -> Result<Url, JssError>;
               fn logout_url(base: &Url) -> Result<Url, JssError>;
               fn csrf_token_url(base: &Url) -> Result<Url, JssError>;
               fn get_logged_user_url(base: &Url) -> Result<Url, JssError>;
               fn app_page_url(base: &Url) -> Result<Url, JssError>;
           }

       Each yields URLs such as:
           /api/method/login
           /api/method/logout
           /api/method/frappe.auth.get_csrf_token
           /api/method/frappe.auth.get_logged_user
           /app

   ReportBuilder
       Built by RjssClient::report(). Allows chaining filters before
       executing a report.

           pub struct ReportBuilder<'a> { … }

       Methods:
           add_filter(mut self, field: &str, value: &str) -> Self
               Adds a (field, value) filter. Can be chained.

           async run_raw(&self) -> Result<String, JssError>
               Runs the report and returns the raw JSON string.

           async run<T: DeserializeOwned>(&self) -> Result<T, JssError>
               Runs the report and deserializes directly into T.

   ResourceBuilder
       Built by RjssClient::doctype(). Builder for document listing with
       filters, field selection, ordering, and pagination.

           pub struct ResourceBuilder<'a> { … }

       Methods:
           filter(mut self, field: &str, operator: &str, value: &str) -> Self
               Adds a filter condition, e.g., filter("status","=","Open").

           fields(mut self, fields: Vec<&str>) -> Self
               Specifies which fields to return (JSON array).

           order_by(mut self, order: &str) -> Self
               Order, e.g., "creation desc".

           limit(mut self, limit: u32) -> Self
               Page size.

           limit_start(mut self, start: u32) -> Self
               Starting index.

           async execute_raw(&self) -> Result<String, JssError>
               Executes and returns raw JSON.

           async execute<T: DeserializeOwned>(&self) -> Result<T, JssError>
               Executes and deserializes into T.

           async all<T: DeserializeOwned>(&self) -> Result<Vec<T>, JssError>
               Automatically paginates with a page size of 200, collecting
               all records into a Vec<T>.

   Additional public types
       UserInfo
           pub struct UserInfo { pub message: UserInfoMessage }
           UserInfoMessage { pub name, email: Option<String>, roles: Vec<String> }
           Used in get_logged_user responses.

       LoginApiResponse, LoginApiMessage
           (internal, not directly exported but used during login parsing.)

USAGE EXAMPLES

   1. Setup and session authentication:

          use librjss::{RjssClient, ClientConfig, AuthMode};
          use secrecy::SecretString;

          let config = ClientConfig {
              base_url: "https://app.example.com".parse().unwrap(),
              auth_mode: AuthMode::Session {
                  email: SecretString::new("user@example.com".into()),
                  password: SecretString::new("secret".into()),
              },
              ..Default::default()
          };
          let mut client = RjssClient::new(config)?;
          client.authenticate().await?;
          println!("Logged in as: {:?}", client.session_info().unwrap().full_name);

   2. Basic GET and POST:

          let body = client.authenticated_get("/api/resource/ToDo").await?;
          let resp = client.authenticated_post(
              "/api/resource/ToDo",
              r#"{"description":"test"}"#
          ).await?;

   3. File upload:

          let image_bytes = std::fs::read("photo.png")?;
          let result = client.upload_file(
              "photo.png", image_bytes, "Customer", "CUST-001", "image"
          ).await?;
          println!("Upload response: {}", result);

   4. File download:

          let bytes = client.download_file("/files/photo.png").await?;
          std::fs::write("local.png", bytes)?;
          // or directly
          client.download_file_to_path("/files/photo.png", Path::new("local.png")).await?;

   5. Running a report:

          #[derive(Deserialize)]
          struct MyReportRow { /* ... */ }
          let rows: Vec<MyReportRow> = client
              .report("Sales Analytics")
              .add_filter("from_date", "2026-01-01")
              .add_filter("to_date", "2026-06-30")
              .run()
              .await?;

   6. Doctype listing with filters:

          let list: serde_json::Value = client
              .doctype("ToDo")
              .filter("status", "=", "Open")
              .fields(vec!["name", "description", "date"])
              .order_by("creation desc")
              .limit(50)
              .execute()
              .await?;

          // Fetch all records
          let all: Vec<ToDo> = client
              .doctype("ToDo")
              .filter("status", "=", "Cancelled")
              .all()
              .await?;

   7. Single document CRUD:

          let doc = client.get_doc("Customer", "CUST-001").await?;

          #[derive(Serialize)]
          struct NewCustomer { customer_name: String, customer_group: String }
          let new_cust = NewCustomer { ... };
          let created = client.create_doc("Customer", &new_cust).await?;

          let updated = client.update_doc("Customer", "CUST-001", &modification).await?;
          let deleted = client.delete_doc("Customer", "OLD-CUST").await?;

   8. Calling a server method:

          use std::collections::HashMap;
          let mut args = HashMap::new();
          args.insert("doctype".into(), "Sales Invoice".into());
          args.insert("docname".into(), "SINV-0001".into());
          let result = client.call_method("frappe.email.send", Some(args)).await?;

   9. Error handling:

          match client.authenticated_get("/api/resource/ToDo").await {
              Err(JssError::ApiError { exc_type, message, status }) => {
                  eprintln!("[{exc_type}] {message} (HTTP {status})");
              }
              Err(JssError::RateLimited { retry_after }) => {
                  let secs = retry_after.unwrap_or(5);
                  tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_secs(secs)).await;
                  // retry
              }
              Err(e) => {
                  eprintln!("Other error: {}", e);
                  let status_code = e.status_code();
                  // ...
              }
              Ok(data) => { /* process data */ }
          }

   10. Accessing boot data:

          if let Some(boot) = client.boot() {
              println!("Site: {}", boot.sitename);
              println!("Roles: {:?}", boot.user.roles);
              for (doctype, perms) in &boot.user.permissions {
                  println!("{} can: {:?}", doctype, perms);
              }
              if client.is_developer_mode() {
                  println!("Developer mode active");
              }
          }

CONFIGURATION (ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES FOR CLI)
     The following variables are used by the cli_auth binary and can be
     adopted in your own applications:

     JSS_BASE_URL            Required. Base URL of the JSS instance.
     JSS_EMAIL               Email for session auth.
     JSS_PASSWORD            Password for session auth.
     JSS_TOKEN_API_KEY       API key for token auth.
     JSS_TOKEN_API_SECRET    API secret for token auth.
     JSS_EXPECTED_SITENAME   Optional. Expected site name; login fails if
                             the boot sitename does not match.
     JSS_REQUIRED_ROLES      Optional. Comma-separated required roles.
     JSS_TIMEOUT_SECS        Request timeout in seconds (default 30).
     JSS_MAX_RETRIES         Maximum retry attempts (default 3).
     JSS_USER_AGENT          Custom User-Agent header.
     JSS_INSECURE_SSL        Set "true" to accept invalid TLS certificates
                             (e.g., self-signed).

MOCK SERVER FOR DEVELOPMENT
     A full mock server is available at examples/jss_mock_server.rs. It
     replicates the behaviour of a real JSS server:

         • POST /api/method/login             → sets cookie + JSON
         • GET  /app                          → HTML with frappe.boot
         • GET  /api/method/frappe.auth.get_logged_user
         • POST /api/method/logout
         • GET  /api/method/frappe.auth.get_csrf_token (417)

     Start it with:

         cargo run --example jss_mock_server

     Then point the client to http://127.0.0.1:8080 and set
     JSS_INSECURE_SSL=true.

TESTING
     Unit tests (no server required):

         cargo test --lib

     Integration tests require the mock server to be running (see above).
     Once the server is up:

         cargo test --test client_tests
         cargo test --test file_tests
         cargo test --test report_tests
         cargo test --test resource_tests

     Or run everything:

         cargo test --workspace

     A fixture real_app_page.html is used in app_parser unit tests.

CI PIPELINE
     The file .github/workflows/ci.yml runs on every push/PR to master:

         • Format check (rustfmt)
         • Lint (clippy -D warnings)
         • cargo check --workspace
         • Unit tests (cargo test --lib)
         • Start mock server → integration tests
         • Release build
         • Upload cli_auth artifact

